article.headline: Arizona 74, Oregon 60
article.story: EUGENE, Ore. -- Derrick Williams had 20 points and 13 rebounds, Nic Wise and Kyle Fogg added 19 points each and Arizona defeated Oregon 74-60 Saturday. Wise scored 14 points in the second half for the Wildcats (9-9, 3-3 Pac-10), who never trailed. He also went 4 for 5 from 3-point range and had six rebounds and five assists. LeKendric Longmire scored 18 points to lead the Ducks (10-7, 2-3), who have lost three straight at home. Wise (5 of 6), Williams (6 of 8) and Fogg (12 of 12) were a combined 23 for 26 from the foul line, and Arizona was 27 for 33 overall. Malcolm Armstead added 16 points and Michael Dunigan scored 14 for Oregon, which was outrebounded 36-28 and shot just 33 percent compared to 51 percent for Arizona.
